tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, and low urine specific gravity, suggesting impaired renal function. There is also glucosuria and ketonuria despite normal blood glucose and low HbA1c, which may indicate renal glycosuria or possible metabolic derangement. Urine is cloudy and brown with ammoniacal odor, but no evidence of infection (negative nitrites/leukocytes). Recommend further nephrological evaluation and assessment for possible underlying renal or metabolic disorders.
